HB 300 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Riser
Abstract: Changes the appraisal threshold for bank-owned property.
Present law requires a bank to obtain a current appraisal of the fair market value of any
immovable property that bank has acquired under certain conditions within a reasonable time
of the acquisition, and every third calendar year thereafter.
Present law allows a bank to conduct evaluations of residential real estate in lieu of
appraisals if that residential real estate is valued at or below $250,000.
Proposed law raises that threshold for appraisals from $250,000 to $400,000.
(Amends R.S. 6:243(C)(1) and (2))
